task.summary: - Updated HE Responses - Added Wrappers Descriptions
- Updated CRUD Handlers - Added PharmacyLocation.cs and LaboratoryLocation.cs
- Added PharmacyLocation and LaboratoryLocation Get list
- Added Patient Consultation CRUD, Wrappers & Driver
- Refactored consultation job orders get list - Added new Pharmacy Request
- Added Laboratory Create & Update - Added Schedule CRUD

Remove redundant 'IsSuccess' properties and unsupported consultation commands
Several data access and pipeline behavior classes have been adjusted to remove redundant 'IsSuccess' properties, which were automatically set to true if their respective operations did not throw exceptions. This property has been found unnecessary because the successful completion of a method without exceptions already implies success.
Also, several unsupported consultation related files were removed from the HealthEssentials project. These classes were deemed unnecessary because the functionality they were intended to provide is now handled differently. Therefore, their presence would only make the application less maintainable and more confusing.
A couple of other minor changes were made to fix coding style inconsistencies according to company's guideline (like removal of a surplus empty line).

Refined Doctor Consultation List and CmdResponse Handling
Core handler for Doctor Consultation List is updated to filter consultation based on "DoctorGuid" providing effective query results specifically to a Doctor.
CmdResponse for both generic and specified type has been enhanced by providing constructors with "HttpStatusCode" and "(optional)message", facilitating direct initial setting of these properties at the time of object creation.
For "GetDoctorHandler.cs", an unnecessary extra line was removed improving code readability.
UpdateDoctorConsultationRequest and CreateDoctorConsultationRequest have field "IsEnabled" added, permitting status updates for a consultation.
To allow filtering by "DoctorGuid", it has been added to "GetDoctorConsultationListRequest". These updates improve data handling and usability of the application.
